*We're convened this November 16th in the matter titled State of Mayflower versus Ewifes, No. CR-189-25. *

Mr. Ewifes, I must ensure you understand your rights during this proceeding:
1. You have the right to remain silent. You do not have to speak or provide any information that could incriminate you.
2. You have the right to an attorney present during any questioning or legal proceedings. If you cannot afford an attorney, one will be appointed for you at no cost.
3. You have the right to a fair public trial where evidence will be presented, and witnesses can be called to testify on your behalf.
4. You have the right to confront witnesses against you and test their evidence. You can question them in court.

Please respond with the following to indicate your understanding of these rights:

I understand my rights as they were read to me.

Ocazius 2025-11-16 02:43 p.m.
The State of Mayflower has charged you with:

COUNT 1
1 M.S.C. 2101 FIRST DEGREE MURDER (FELONY)
The offence of first degree murder applies to those who intentionally and maliciously
kills another person with premeditation, or who kills whilst in the commission of a felony, or
who kills a uniformed or clearly identifiable civil servant in the commission of their duties.
On or about 12 October 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did shoot a
uniformed deputy of the Clark County Sheriffs Office with a Mayflower National Guard-issued
R21M rifle, causing the death of the deputy. The deputy was killed as an on-duty civil servant.

COUNT 2

1 M.S.C. 2302 ASSAULT WITH A DEADLY WEAPON (FELONY)
The offence of assault with a deadly weapon applies to those who assault a person with
an object capable of causing severe harm to the person.

1

On or about 12 October 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did shoot a
uniformed deputy of the Clark County Sheriffs Office with a Mayflower National Guard-issued
R21M rifle, causing the death of the deputy. This rifle is a weapon designed for military
operations, capable of inflicting severe bodily harm.

COUNT 3
1 M.S.C. 3104 GRAND THEFT (FELONY)
The offence of grand theft applies to those who steal another's property with a value of
over $200, including local, county, or state issued equipment to public services; or the theft of a
firearm.
On or about 12 October 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did
unlawfully remove a Mayflower National Guard R21M rifle, a firearm, from the control and
possession of the National Guard contrary to law and military regulations by using it off the
National Guard team and out of uniform. The rifle was also placed in the trunk of the personal
vehicle of EWIFES, contrary to 3 M.S.C. 4 1602(a)(i). The firearm was later used to kill a
public servant.
Ocazius 2025-11-16 02:43 p.m.
COUNT 4

1 M.S.C. 6102 UNLICENSED POSSESSION OF A FIREARM (FELONY)
The offence of unlicensed possession of a firearm applies to those who possess a firearm
without holding an active state-issued firearms license, or who possesses a restricted-grade
firearm as designated by the Attorney General and who is not authorized to do so as prescribed
under 4 M.S.C. 5 4402.
On or about 12 October 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did
unlawfully remove a Mayflower National Guard R21M rifle, a firearm, from the control and
possession of the National Guard contrary to law and military regulations by using it off the
National Guard team and out of uniform. The rifle was also placed in the trunk of the personal
vehicle of EWIFES, contrary to 3 M.S.C. 4 1602(a)(i). The firearm was later used to kill a
public servant.
Ocazius 2025-11-16 02:43 p.m.
At all times relevant to the offences on or about 12 October 2025, defendant EWIFES
was a member of the Mayflower National Guard, and was handling a firearm belonging to and
issued by the Mayflower National Guard (namely, an R21M rifle), satisfying statutory
jurisdictional requirements for prosecution under 3 M.S.C. 4 3202(e).

In relation to events occurring on or about 16 October 2025:

COUNT 5, 6, 7, 8, 9
1 M.S.C. 2102 SECOND DEGREE MURDER (FELONY)
The offence of second degree murder applies to those who intentionally kill another
person with intent to kill or commit great bodily harm.
On or about 16 October 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did
deliberately detonate a remote controlled explosive (also known as a jerry bomb) using a
device under the care and control of the defendant, resulting in the immediate deaths of an
off-duty Mayflower National Guard guardsman and four on-duty Mayflower National Guard
guardsmen.

COUNT 10

1 M.S.C. 6301 DISCHARGING OF A DESTRUCTIVE DEVICE CAUSING DEATH OR
BODILY HARM (FELONY)
The offence of discharging of a destructive device causing death or bodily harm applies
to those who discharge a device containing an explosive ordinance which causes death or bodily
harm to another.
On or about 16 October 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did
deliberately detonate a remote controlled explosive (also known as a jerry bomb) using a
device under the care and control of the defendant, resulting in the immediate deaths of an
off-duty Mayflower National Guard guardsman and four on-duty Mayflower National Guard
guardsmen.
Ocazius 2025-11-16 02:43 p.m.
At all times relevant to the offences on or about 16 October 2025, defendant EWIFES
was a member of the Mayflower National Guard, and was physically located in the Fort Standish
military installation controlled by the National Guard, satisfying statutory jurisdictional
requirements for prosecution under 3 M.S.C. 4 3202(b).

In relation to events occurring on or about 3 November 2025:

COUNT 11
1 M.S.C. 2102 SECOND DEGREE MURDER (FELONY)
The offence of second degree murder applies to those who intentionally kill another
person with intent to kill or commit great bodily harm.
On or about 3 November 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did use a
XR21 rifle issued by the Mayflower National Guard to shoot and kill a civilian engaged in
fishing around the Fort Standish military installation without lawful excuse and contrary to
military regulations. At no time relevant to the offence was the civilian engaged in behaviour that
was threatening to any person or property.
Ocazius 2025-11-16 02:43 p.m.
COUNT 12, 13

1 M.S.C. 2302 ASSAULT WITH A DEADLY WEAPON (FELONY)
The offence of assault with a deadly weapon applies to those who assault a person with
an object capable of causing severe harm to the person.
On or about 3 November 2025, within the County of Clark, defendant EWIFES did use a
XR21 rifle issued by the Mayflower National Guard to shoot and kill a civilian engaged in
fishing around the Fort Standish military installation without lawful excuse and contrary to
military regulations. At no time relevant to the offence was the civilian engaged in behaviour that
was threatening to any person or property. Another civilian was in close proximity to the civilian
who was shot. The two civilians were under reasonable fear of imminent injury as they came
under fire from defendant EWIFES, having bullets strike near where they were standing.

4

At all times relevant to the offences on or about 3 November 2025, defendant EWIFES
was a member of the Mayflower National Guard, was physically located in the Fort Standish
military installation controlled by the National Guard, and was on the Mayflower National Guard
team in-game, satisfying statutory jurisdictional requirements for prosecution under 3 M.S.C. 4
3202(a) and 3 M.S.C. 4 3202(b).
